OL,3,CMetropolitan Police cannot sack
OL,4,Cofficers by removing vetting clearance
OL,6,F"Dismissal is a matter which should be
OL,7,Fprovided for in regulations made by
OL,8,Fthe Secretary of State. This results
OL,9,Fin an anomalous situation where
OL,10,Fofficers who do not have basic vetting
OL,11,Fclearance cannot be dismissed by the
OL,12,Fdefendant.
OL,14,F"In my view, that anomaly could and
OL,15,Fshould be resolved by regulations."
OL,17,FLawyers for the Metropolitan Police
OL,18,Fhad previously told the court that a
OL,19,Fprocedure under current performance
OL,20,Fregulations allowed officers to be
OL,21,Fdismissed if clearance was withdrawn.
