OL,6,F"If a finding of gross incompetence is
OL,7,Fmade, before an outcome is determined,
OL,8,Fthe panel must have regard to the
OL,9,Fofficer's personal record and any
OL,10,Fmitigation or references he may put
OL,11,Fforward, but this is meaningless if
OL,12,Fthe only available outcome is
OL,13,Fdismissal."
OL,15,FThe judge concluded: "In my view,
OL,16,Fdismissal without notice for gross
OL,17,Fincompetence will be a serious stain
OL,18,Fon a police officer's record when
OL,19,Fseeking alternative employment, in
OL,20,Faddition to the loss of vetting
OL,21,Fclearance.
